Powell Functions

This report includes Powell functions that have been documented as of April 19, 2017.


Specifically, these functions were edited and updated to reflect the LTEMP ROD and documentation is being added during that updated process.

1 Powell Functions

Functions are included in alphabetical order. The Powell.MonthlyReleaseTable is included at the beginning of this section because many of the functions rely on it.

1.1 Powell Functions for Computing Yearly and Monthly Releases per IG

Initial group of Powell functions used for computing yearly and monthly releases. Specifically, these are functions that were edited to reflect the LTEMP ROD.

1.1.6 ComputePowellRelease

Arguments:
- NUMERIC equalizationRelease: Powell's additional release to equalize/balance

Returns:
Monthly flow (numeric)

Description:
Based on the remaining forecast WY release, set Powell's release by using the set monthly release patterns found in Powell Monthly Release Tables. Note that the release's won't always (ever) equal the releases from the tables as the WY release is not likely to be exactly equal to one of the tiers, and the tiers can switch from month to month.

Return Type: NUMERIC

Arguments:

  • NUMERIC equalizationRelease

Body

Constraints

Referenced Functions

  • GetMaxReleaseGivenInflow
  • MinRelease
  • ForecastPowellRelease
  • GetPowellMonthlyProportion
  • VolumeToFlow

1.1.7 ComputePowellReleaseBalancing

Arguments:
- NUMERIC equalizationRelease: the release necessary to equalize/balance
- STRING minRelease: minimum constrained release from Powell, e.g., "700"
- STRING maxRelease: maximum constrained release from Powell, e.g., "950"

Returns:
Monthly flow (numeric)

Description:
Computes the monthly balancing release from Powell if in either the Upper or Lower Elevation Balancing Tiers. NOTE: the release is constrained by the specified min and max release for that tier. This specified release is the STRING argument minRelease and maxRelease.

Return Type: NUMERIC

Arguments:

  • NUMERIC equalizationRelease
  • STRING minRelease
  • STRING maxRelease

Body

1.1.13 GetPowellMonthlyProportion

Arguments:
- NUMERIC remainingWYReleaseForecast: remaining Powell WY release forecast as volume

Returns:
Proportion (numeric)

Description:
Given the remaining forecast WY release from Powell (including the current month), and the release up through the previous month, use the total WY release forecast to select the appropriate column from the Powell Release Tables. The monthy proportion of the current month is then computed based on the release volumes from the release tables for the reaming months in the WY.

Return Type: NUMERIC

Arguments:

  • NUMERIC remainingWYReleaseForecast

Body

Referenced Functions

  • SumTableColumn
  • SumFlowsToVolume
  • GetPowellReleaseColumnIndex
  • GetWYMonthNumber

1.1.15 GetWYMonthNumber

Parameters:
- DATETIME month

Returns:
Numeric: The month number based on water year counting instead of calendar year counting.

Description:
Given any date, returns the water year month number instead of the calendar year month number returned by GetMonth(). Ex: January will return 4 instead of 1.

Example:

GeyWYMonthNumber(@"January, 2017") returns 4

Return Type: NUMERIC

Arguments:

  • DATETIME month

1.1.17 PowellComputeRunoffSeasonRelease

Arguments:
none

Returns:
Monthly volume (numeric)

Description:
This function computes the release for the month, from the spring outflow volume and the release
weights. It is constrained by the minimum and maximum release.

On March 4, 2000, TJF added the check to see if the outflow volume average (equally distributed over the remaining
months) exceeds a check (currently 1 maf). If so, we want to just equally weight the outflow for the remaining months.
This was added for high forecast years, where we really would want to start dumping the water quicker than what the
current weights would have us do.

2014-03-15, RAB: This function does not match the description included in Appendix A of the 2007 FEIS (language included below). The above description is reflected in the logic, but the appendix doucmentation suggests that if the release is computed as > 1 MAF it would be held to 1 MAF. We think the text in the Appendix is probably wrong and the logic here is consistent with the description from TJF on 2000-03-04.

2007 FEIS Appendix A, Section A.5.2, Final Paragraph
...
An additional constraint is placed on computed monthly release during spill avoidance. If the calculated average flow for a given month is in excess of 1.0 maf, then it is held to a maximum of 1.0 maf each month.

Return Type: NUMERIC

Arguments: None

Body

Constraints

Referenced Functions

  • SumTableColumn
  • SumFlowsToVolume
  • MinRelease
  • MaxRelease
  • GetPowellReleaseColumnIndex
  • PowellSpringOutflowVolume
  • GetWYMonthNumber
  • VolumeToFlow

1.1.18 PowellMinObjRelforCurrentMonth

Arguments:
none

Returns:
Monthly volume (numeric)

Description:
Returns the monthly release volume from an 8.23 release pattern. If the release through the previous month has been exactly according to an 8.23 release pattern, then it will return the expected release volume based on the 8.23 table. Otherwise, it will scale the current month's release to ensure the remaining WY release is the same shape as the remaining 8.23 release shape.

Return Type: NUMERIC

Arguments: None

Body

Constraints

Referenced Functions

  • MinRelease
  • GetWYMonthNumber
  • PowellMinObjRelVolRemaining
  • ComputeMinObjReleaseRemaining
  • VolumeToFlow

1.1.24 PowellReleaseStringToVolume

Arguments:
- STRING relStr: Powell release as string (to three digits)

Returns:
Annual volume (numeric)

Description:
A set Powell Release,e.g., 823 or 700, is an argument as a string. The arguement is converted to a volume.

Example:
PowellReleaseStringToVolume("823") -> 8230000 acre-ft

Return Type: NUMERIC

Arguments:

  • STRING relStr

Body
